    [:ul {:id "48659f7d-2c8f-4875-8f95-6603ff831a72"
          :class "bulleted-list"}
     [:li {:style {"listStyleType" "disc"}}
      "Sharing accurate and up-to-date data."]]
    [:ul {:id "16489b31-c2cb-4166-8c0d-a7935cdfdd93"
          :class "bulleted-list"}
     [:li {:style {"listStyleType" "disc"}}
      "All stakeholders that are responsible for the data should be available and willing to extract the required data and invest the necessary time to answer our questions while exploring them."]]
    [:h2 {:id "eadd526b-15f8-4ab4-a774-67c534f7cf97"
          :class ""}
     "3. Shared Commitment to Success:"]
    [:h3 {:id "df09a968-fa68-4e38-a718-b420ee78fd66"
          :class ""}
     "What it entails"]
    [:p {:id "4e9041f7-2570-422b-932a-08bbb4ac1556"
         :class ""}
     "We are fully committed to your success, and we expect the same level of commitment from you. This means that our financial results will depend on the success of our collaboration. This linkage will be established in the contract, aligning our profitability with your success. Additionally, our reputation and brand image depend on achieving high-quality outcomes."]
    [:p {:id "1b2ab8b4-dfa6-497e-8fe7-977566697a37"
         :class ""}
     "However, one-sided commitment rarely leads to success; your team and organization should also be equally committed to the results. You may have mechanisms to interest your teams on results, as far as it is possible, we should reorient those mechanisms on the project’s goal."]
    [:h3 {:id "8cde6bca-5405-443f-9cf6-d4c55863a17f"
          :class ""}
     "Why it is necessary?"]
    [:ul {:id "33c81f0b-d9d3-4775-b9d4-ac5153f7fee3"
          :class "bulleted-list"}
     [:li {:style {"listStyleType" "disc"}}
      "Formalizing the commitment allows us to clearly define expectations, manage potential over-expectations, and maximize the chances of achieving the desired outcomes."]]
    [:ul {:id "71cbd1ca-eca7-4a93-abd3-8e39fd2986c9"
          :class "bulleted-list"}
     [:li {:style {"listStyleType" "disc"}}
      "If your teams are genuinely committed, we can work together towards the common goal. Creating this collaborative mindset is key to success."]]
    [:h3 {:id "7de40255-ad0b-4bd3-bc2b-350142ed03cb"
          :class ""}
     "Implications for you"]
    [:ul {:id "5453cab8-3042-4b7e-ad00-aa0d3b579b48"
          :class "bulleted-list"}
     [:li {:style {"listStyleType" "disc"}}
      "Contracts will include bonuses tied to the level of success achieved."]]
    [:ul {:id "bc2d2cea-5df4-461d-87e3-e44a0bf58b6c"
          :class "bulleted-list"}
     [:li {:style {"listStyleType" "disc"}}
      "Your team's objectives will be linked to this commitment, potentially affecting the bonuses for those who have them."]]
    [:h1 {:id "d3c05bfc-db71-4395-a92e-9e8878606a88"
          :class ""}
     "Conclusion"]
    [:p {:id "8a929524-b285-4737-a1d1-3f84527134ac"
         :class ""}
     "If any of the aforementioned commitments are not met, it may indicate that the timing is not suitable for collaboration. In such cases, we prefer to stop the project as meeting established goals would not be feasible."]
    [:p {:id "4397979e-9a10-4f37-9287-b51c2b029aaa"
         :class ""}
     "We want to avoid situations where projects continue despite not meeting many requirements, as it ultimately harms the company. Making a decision to stop a project, when necessary, is a sign of responsible decision-making, and maturity. It should bring confidence to you, as it signifies our commitment to transparency."]
    [:p {:id "a18a23ec-e868-4159-9abe-9caf4661b78c"
         :class ""}
     "A stopped project should not be regarded as the end of our future collaboration. Instead, it indicates that the conditions at that time were not suitable for moving forward. This approach allows us to maintain transparency and ensure that future endeavors are pursued under more favorable circumstances."]]])

